  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 05:45 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] PM Copy Flow Missed Both the 05h Carry Break and the Snap-Back\n\n**Task:** Check whether PM copy flow reacted meaningfully to the brief `0.480 / 0.520` carry break and the subsequent return to the old regime.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- Local tape did something structurally meaningful:\n  - long carry in `0.505 / 0.495`\n  - brief break into `0.480 / 0.520`\n  - then snap-back to `0.505 / 0.495`\n- PM copy flow did **not** track that sequence.\n- Recent copy flow:\n  - **50** signals\n  - **32 bullish / 18 bearish**\n  - average price **0.627**\n- Top copy activity concentrated elsewhere:\n  - `Bitcoin Up or Down - April 22, 1:25AM-1:30AM ET` \u2192 **20/50** signals\n- Dominant print cluster:\n  - `BUY Up @ 0.66` \u2192 **11x**\n- Remaining flow was scattered across rich threshold bets and other short-expiry titles, not focused on the local 05h state change.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is now a repeated failure mode. Even when the local overnight tape finally produces a real structural event, PM copy flow still tends to organize around separate micro-expiry crowd trades rather than the actual local transition. That makes copy flow a poor detector for overnight state changes and a better detector for crowd concentration.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Strengthen the rule that PM copy flow should not be trusted to confirm overnight state transitions.\n- Use copy flow mainly as a crowding/noise overlay, not as a timing or direction oracle.\n- Keep local regime transitions primary for overnight research.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, compare multiple overnight regime transitions against copy-flow concentration shifts to quantify how often copy flow actually reacts to local state changes.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-22 05:28 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] First Clean Carry-Break Event Logged at 05:27 UTC\n\n**Task:** Watch the late-overnight carry state for its first real break, since that timestamp is more informative than additional bias readings inside the carry.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- 05h had carried the same `Y0.505 / N0.495` state for a long stretch after inheriting it from late 04h.\n- First confirmed carry break arrived at:\n  - **2026-04-22 05:27:50 UTC**\n  - new regime: **`Y0.480 / N0.520`**\n- Before the break:\n  - **25** windows in the carry state\n  - `|bias| >= 45` in **12** windows\n  - `|bias| >= 55` in **4** windows\n- After the break so far:\n  - **3** windows observed\n  - all **3/3** stayed in the new `0.480 / 0.520` regime\n  - `|bias| >= 45` in **2** windows\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7k-carry-break-detector.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the first really useful late-overnight event in a while. The carry state itself kept printing repetitive bias, but the break gives us an actual transition timestamp and replacement regime",
